obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (5108)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186&sectionId=5108&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called The Central Boards of Revenue`
  line `Act, 1963.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st January, 1964, vide notification No. S.O. 3606, dated 30th December 1963, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary Part II,`
  line `sec. 3 (ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (5109)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186&sectionId=5109&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means the Central Board of Direct Taxes or ^1[the Central Board of Indirect Taxes and`
  line `Customs] constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Central Board of Revenue" means the Central Board of Revenue constituted under the`
  line `Central Board of Revenue Act, 1924 (4 of 1924).`
  line
  line `(c) "direct tax" means--`
  line
  line `(1) any duty leviable or tax chargeable under--`
  line
  line `(i) the Estate Duty Act, 1953 (34 of 1953);`
  line
  line `(ii) the Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957);`
  line
  line `(iii) the Expenditure-tax Act, 1957 (29 of 1957);`
  line
  line `(iv) the Gift-tax Act, 1958 (18 of 1958);`
  line
  line `(v) the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(vi) the Super Profits Tax Act, 1963 (14 of 1963);`
  line ^2***
  line
  line `^3[(vii) the Interest-tax Act, 1974 (45 of 1974);`
  line ^4***]
  line
  line `^5[(viii) the Hotel-Receipts Tax Act, 1980 (54 of 1980);`
  line ^6***]
  line
  line `^7[(ix) the Expenditure-tax Act, 1987 (35 of 1987);`
  line ^8***]
  line
  line `^9[(x) the Black Money (Undisclosed Foreign Income and Assets) and Imposition of Tax`
  line `Act, 2015 (22 of 2015); and]`
  line
  line `(2) any other duty or tax which, having regard to its nature or incidence, may be declared by the`
  line `Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, to be a direct tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s.160, for "the Central Board of Excise and Customs" (w.e.f 29-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The word "and" omitted by Act 45 of 1974, s. 30 (w.e.f. 23-9-1974).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 30, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-9-1974).`
  line
  line `4. The word "and" omitted by Act 54 of 1980, s. 37 (w.e.f. 9-12-1980).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 37, ibid. (w.e.f. 9-12-1980).`
  line
  line `6. The word "and" omitted by Act 35 of 1987, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-11-1987).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 33, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-1987).`
  line
  line `8. The word "and" omitted by Act 22 of 2015, s. 87 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by s. 87, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (5110)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of separate Central Boards for Direct Taxes and for Indirect Taxes and Customs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186&sectionId=5110&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `3. Constitution of separate Central Boards for Direct Taxes and for ^1[Indirect Taxes and`
  line `Customs].--(1) The Central Government shall, in place of the Central Board of Revenue, constitute two`
  line `separate Boards of Revenue to be called the Central Board of Direct Taxes and ^2[the Central Board of`
  line `Indirect Taxes and Customs], and each such Board shall, subject to the control of the Central`
  line `Government, exercise such powers and perform such duties, as may be entrusted to that Board by the`
  line `Central Government or by or under any law.`
  line
  line `(2) Each Board shall consist of such number of persons ^3[not exceeding seven] as the Central`
  line `Government may think fit to appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 160, for "Excise and Customs" (w.e.f 29-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 160, ibid., for "the Central Board of Excise and Customs" (w.e.f 29-3-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 1978, s. 27 for "and not exceeding five" (w.e.f. 21-6-1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (5111)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Procedure of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186&sectionId=5111&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may make rules for the purpose of`
  line `regulating the transaction of business by each Board and every order made or act done in accordance with`
  line `such rules shall be deemed to be the order or act, as the case may be, of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session in which it is so laid or the`
  line `session immediately following, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses`
  line `agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or`
  line `be of no effect, as the case may be, so however, that any modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (5112)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Amendment of certain enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 160, ibid., for "the Central Board of Excise and Customs" (w.e.f 29-3-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186&sectionId=5112&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the Estate Duty Act, 1953 (34 of 1953), the`
  line `Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957), the Expenditure-tax Act,1957 (29 of 1957 ), the Gift-tax Act, 1958`
  line `(18 of 1958), the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), and the Super Profits Tax Act, 1963 (14 of 1963)`
  line `for the words and figures "Central Board of Revenue constituted under the Central Board of Revenue Act,`
  line `1924 (4 of 1924)" or "Central Board of Revenue", wherever they occur, the words and figures "Central`
  line `Board of Direct Taxes constituted under the Central Boards of Revenue Act, 1963" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(2) In the Central Excises and Salt Act, 1944 (1 of 1944), and the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962),`
  line `for the words and figures "Central Board of Revenue constituted under the Central Board of Revenue Act,`
  line `1924 (4 of 1924)" or "Central Board of Revenue" wherever they occur, the words and figures ^1[the`
  line `Central Board of Indirect Taxes and Customs] constituted under the Central Boards of Revenue Act,`
  line `1963" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(3) The functions entrusted to the Central Board of Revenue by or under any other enactment`
  line shall,--
  line
  line `(a) if such functions relate to matters connected with direct taxes, be discharged by the Central`
  line `Board of Direct Taxes; and`
  line
  line `(b) if such functions relate to any other matter, unless they are entrusted by the Central`
  line `Government to the Central Board of Direct Taxes, be discharged by the ^1[the Central Board of`
  line `Indirect Taxes and Customs].`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (5113)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Transfer of certain proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186&sectionId=5113&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every proceeding pending at the commencement of this`
  line `Act, before the Central Board of Revenue shall--`
  line
  line `(a) if it is a proceeding relating to direct taxes, stand transferred to the Central Board of Direct`
  line `Taxes; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case stand transferred to the ^1[the Central Board of Indirect Taxes and Customs].`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any proceeding stands transferred to the Central Board of`
  line `Direct Taxes or to ^1[the Central Board of Indirect Taxes and Customs], it shall be referred to the Central`
  line `Government whose decision thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) In any legal proceeding pending at the commencement of this Act to which the Central Board of`
  line `Revenue is a party,--`
  line
  line `(a) if it is a proceeding relating to direct taxes, the Central Board of Direct Taxes shall be deemed`
  line `to be substituted for the Central Board of Revenue in such proceeding; and`
  line
  line `(b) if it is a proceeding relating to any other matter, ^2[the Central Board of Indirect Taxes and`
  line `Customs] shall be deemed to be substituted for the Central Board of Revenue in such proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 160, ibid., for "the Central Board of Excise and Customs" (w.e.f 29-3-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 160, for "the Central Board of Excise and Customs" (w.e.f 29-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (5114)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186&sectionId=5114&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the purposes of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the`
  line difficulty.
  line
  line `(2) An order under sub-section (1) may be made so as to have retrospective effect from a date not`
  line `earlier than the date of the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (5115)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 160, for "the Central Board of Excise and Customs" (w.e.f 29-3-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186&sectionId=5115&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00004_196354_1517807318186
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Board of Revenue Act, 1924 (4 of 1924), of is hereby`
  line repealed.
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall affect any appointment, assessment, order (including`
  line `quasi-judicial order) or rule made, or exemption, approval or recognition granted, or any notice,`
  line `notification, direction or instruction issued, or any duty levied, or penalty or fine imposed, or confiscation`
  line `adjudged, or any form prescribed, or any other thing done or action taken by the Central Board of`
  line `Revenue under any law and any such appointment, assessment, order, rule, exemption, approval,`
  line `recognition, notice, notification, direction, instruction, duty, penalty, fine, confiscation, form, thing or`
  line `action shall be deemed to have been made, granted, issued, levied, imposed, adjudged, prescribed, done`
  line `or taken by the Central Board of Direct Taxes, or as the case may be, by ^1[the Central Board of Indirect`
  line `Taxes and Customs] and shall continue to be in force unless and until it is revised, withdrawn or`
  line `superseded by the concerned Board.`
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
